SUMMARY:NJ Audubon: Botany Blitz at Hawk Rise
DESCRIPTION:Led by Angus Macaulay\, NJ Audubon Teacher Naturalist \nJoin us on the trail where we will identify as many plants as we can and discuss what we find. Hawk Rise is home to countless plant species – both native and exotic. Join us on the trail where we will identify as many plants as we can and discuss what we find. Downloading an identification app such as iNaturalist is helpful but not required. This program is appropriate for individuals of all ages. Come dressed for the weather. Beverages will be served afterwards. \nRegistration required at Eventbrite by 4/11/26 at 4:00 PM. \nCOST: FREE \nInterested in becoming an NJ Audubon member? Please click on the following link to learn more or join: Become a Member today! \nCANCELLATION: NJA/CMBO programs require a minimum number of registrants to run\, five days in advance of the start of the tour but are seldom cancelled. If we do cancel\, due to lack of participation\, severe weather\, or unforeseen circumstances\, we notify all participants in advance\, and all are eligible for a full credit or refund. Participants may cancel without penalty if greater than 30 days in advance. Cancellations 10 to 30 days in advance may be subject to a 25% service charge. No refunds or credits for cancellations less than ten days in advance unless due to health emergencies. \nREGISTER HERE
